\b\fs36 Host Alert Conditions:\par

\pard{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\fs28 Host is Down :\b0\fs24 Sends an alert if Atlas is unable to reach a host for several minutes.\b\fs36\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b0\fs24             This alert is generally triggered by one of the following conditions:\par

\pard{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li1080\sa200\sl276\slmult1 The cluster has experienced a failure and is being auto-healed.\par
